HEADWORD: Sawbuck
<hw>Saw"buck`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A
sawhorse.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <ety>[Colloq., from the Roman X for ten, like the support
of a <ets>sawbuck</ets>.]</ety> <def>a ten-dollar bill; also,
<col><b>double sawbuck</b></col>, a twenty-dollar bill.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

